The evidence with the title 'Does obama pay dog trainer $102,000 at tax payer expense? ' says It's not true. This accusation gained popularity as the 2012 election cycle heated up . There was a popular chain email entitled “ Barack Obama's 32 month report card by Rich Carroll ” which many assertions were made , including: “ first president to keep a dog trainer on retainer for $ 102,000.00 a year at taxpayer expense . ”.
